'''Ladysmith, Kansas''' is an unincorporated populated place in [[Clay County, Kansas]]. The town is located south of Clay Center and Idana.

==History==    
A post office was opened in Ladysmith in 1900, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1906.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kshs.org/geog/geog_postoffices/search/county:CY |title=Kansas Post Offices, 1828-1961 (archived) |publisher=Kansas Historical Society |accessdate=7 June 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009130019/http://www.kshs.org/geog/geog_postoffices/search/county%3ACY |archivedate=October 9, 2013 |df= }}</ref>

